import{_ as o,o as t,c as r,a as c,d as e,e as n,b as i}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const s={},l=e("h1",{id:"why-is-hiv-so-hard-to-kill",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#why-is-hiv-so-hard-to-kill","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),n(" Why is HIV So Hard to Kill ?")],-1),a=i('<p>HIV, the virus that causes AIDS, is a master of <code>disguise</code>.</p><p>It has the ability to change its outer coat of <code>proteins</code> frequently.</p><p>This quick-change act makes it hard for the <code>immune</code> system to <code>recognise</code> it and destroy it.</p><p>But what makes HIV even harder to kill is that it targets one of the most important cells in the immune system for <em>fighting infection</em>.</p><p><code>Technically</code> called a CD4+ cell, this cell is more commonly known as a <em>Helper T cell</em>.</p><p>You can think of Helper T cells as the air traffic controllers of the immune system.</p><p>The immune system&#39;s job is to protect the body from dangerous <code>traitors</code>, like cancer, and harmful <code>intruders</code>, like viruses and bacteria.</p><p><code>Overlapping</code> networks of immune cells are <code>constantly</code> talking to each other and <code>coordinating</code> their efforts.</p><p>It&#39;s a lot like airplanes <code>zipping</code> around in a busy airspace.</p><p>The Helper T cells sit at the heart of many of these networks.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 导致艾滋病的HIV病毒是伪装大师。<br> 它有能力频繁地改变它的外层蛋白质。<br> 这种快速变化的行为使得免疫系统很难识别并摧毁它。<br> 但让HIV更难被杀死的是，它的目标是免疫系统中对抗感染的最重要的细胞之一。<br> 技术上称为CD4+细胞，这种细胞通常被称为辅助性T细胞。<br> 你可以把辅助性T细胞想象成免疫系统的空中交通管制员。<br> 免疫系统的工作是保护身体免受危险的叛徒，如癌症，和有害的入侵者，如病毒和细菌。<br> 重叠的免疫细胞网络不断地相互交谈并协调它们的努力。<br> 这很像飞机在繁忙的空域中快速飞行。<br> 辅助性T细胞位于这些网络的核心。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> fighting infection -&gt; 抗感染：指身体对抗病原体入侵的过程，包括免疫系统的反应和药物治疗等手段。<br> Helper T cell -&gt; 辅助性T细胞</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> isguise ( disguising, disguised, disguises )<br><code>英 [dɪsˈɡaɪz]美 [dɪsˈɡaɪz]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 假扮，伪装；掩饰，隐瞒<br> n. 伪装物，伪装</p></blockquote><p>protein [ 复数 proteins ]<br><code>英 [ˈprəʊtiːn]美 [ˈproʊtiːn]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 蛋白质，朊<br> adj. 蛋白质的</p></blockquote><p>immune<br><code>英 [ɪˈmjuːn]美 [ɪˈmjuːn]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 免疫的；不受影响的；免除的，豁免的<br> n. 免疫者，免除者</p></blockquote><p>recognise<br><code>英 [ˈrekəɡnaɪz]美 [ˈrekəɡnaɪz]</code></p><blockquote><p>vt. 认出；承认，认可；识别</p></blockquote><p>technically<br><code>英 [ˈteknɪkli]美 [ˈteknɪkli]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 技术上；专门地；学术上；工艺上</p></blockquote><p>traitor [ 复数 traitors ]<br><code>英 [ˈtreɪtə(r)]美 [ˈtreɪtər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 叛徒，卖国贼</p></blockquote><p>intruder [ 复数 intruders ]<br><code>英 [ɪnˈtruːdə(r)]美 [ɪnˈtruːdər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 闯入者，侵入者；不速之客</p></blockquote><p>overlapping<br><code>英 [ˌəʊvəˈlæpɪŋ]美 [ˌoʊvərˈlæpɪŋ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 重叠；与……重合（overlap 的现在分词）</p></blockquote><p>constantly<br><code>英 [ˈkɒnstəntli]美 [ˈkɑːnstəntli]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 总是，经常地，不断地</p></blockquote><p>coordinate ( coordinating, coordinated, coordinates )<br><code>英 [kəʊˈɔːdɪneɪt]美 [koʊˈɔːrdɪneɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 协调，配合；使身体协调；（使颜色、款式、风格等）搭配，配套；给 （原子或分子）配位，与……形成共价键<br> n. 坐标；配套服装；同等级（或类别）的人（或事物）<br> adj. 地位相当的，同等重要的；（语法）并列的；（化学）配位的</p></blockquote><p>zipping ( zipping, zipped, zips )<br><code>美 [ˈzɪpɪŋ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 拉上拉链；用拉链锁上；快速移动；压缩（zip 的现在分词）</p></blockquote></details><p>It does things like tell one group of immune cells, the Killer T cells, to target HIV and destroy it.</p><p>Or Helper T cells tell another group of immune defenders, the <em>so called</em> B Cells, to make <code>antibodies</code> that attack the virus.</p><p>Now imagine if all the air traffic controllers started to disappear one by one.</p><p><em>None of</em> the other cells in the remaining networks would know where to go or what to do.</p><p>The whole system would have trouble fighting not just HIV but many other illnesses as well.</p><p><code>Indeed</code>, that&#39;s what we see in people with AIDS.</p><p>They become sick with <code>ailments</code> our immune system is usually better at <em>fighting off</em>.</p><p><code>Tuberculosis</code>, <code>meningitis</code>, <em>rare forms</em> of <code>pneumonia</code>, <em>non-Hodgkin&#39;s <code>lymphoma</code></em>, and <code>cervical</code> cancer.</p><p>HIV doesn&#39;t <em>fight fair</em>.</p><p>It attacks the very cells that would coordinate its destruction.</p><p>In order to boost the immune system against HIV, we need to get the Helper T cells back in control.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 它会告诉一组免疫细胞，杀手T细胞，以艾滋病毒为目标并摧毁它。<br> 辅助性T细胞告诉另一组免疫防御者，即所谓的B细胞，制造攻击病毒的抗体。<br> 现在想象一下，如果所有的空中交通管制员开始一个接一个地消失。<br> 剩下的网络中的其他细胞都不知道该去哪里或做什么。<br> 整个系统不仅会在对抗艾滋病病毒方面遇到困难，还会在对抗许多其他疾病方面遇到困难。<br> 事实上，这就是我们在艾滋病患者身上看到的。<br> 他们患上了我们的免疫系统通常能更好地抵御的疾病。<br> 肺结核，脑膜炎，罕见肺炎，非霍奇金淋巴瘤和宫颈癌。<br> 艾滋病毒的斗争并不公平。<br> 它攻击那些能协调其毁灭的细胞。<br> 为了增强免疫系统对抗HIV，我们需要让辅助性T细胞重新控制。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> so called -&gt; 所谓的<br> None of -&gt; 没有任何一个；无一例外<br> fighting off -&gt; 抵御，击退<br> rare forms -&gt; 罕见的形式<br> non-Hodgkin&#39;s lymphoma -&gt; 非霍奇金淋巴瘤<br> fight fair -&gt; 公平竞争</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> antibodies<br><code>美 [ˈæntibɑːdiz]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. [免疫]抗体（antibody 的复数）</p></blockquote><p>indeed<br><code>英 [ɪnˈdiːd]美 [ɪnˈdiːd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 确实，的确；实际上；真正地；&lt;非正式&gt; 真的吗（表示惊讶或觉得某事物荒谬）</p></blockquote><p>ailments<br><code>美 [ˈeɪlmənts]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 疾病，小病（ailment 复数形式）</p></blockquote><p>tuberculosis<br><code>英 [tjuːˌbɜːkjuˈləʊsɪs]美 [tuːˌbɜːrkjəˈloʊsɪs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 结核病（尤指肺结核）</p></blockquote><p>meningitis [ 复数 meningitides ]<br><code>英 [ˌmenɪnˈdʒaɪtɪs]美 [ˌmenɪnˈdʒaɪtɪs]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 脑膜炎</p></blockquote><p>pneumonia<br><code>英 [njuːˈməʊniə]美 [nuːˈmoʊniə]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 肺炎</p></blockquote><p>lymphoma [ 复数 lymphomas或lymphomata ]<br><code>英 [lɪmˈfəʊmə]美 [lɪmˈfoʊmə]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. [肿瘤] 淋巴瘤</p></blockquote><p>cervical<br><code>英 [ˈsɜːvɪk(ə)l]美 [ˈsɜːrvɪk(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 颈的；子宫颈的</p></blockquote></details>',23);function d(p,b){return t(),r("div",null,[l,c(" 为什么艾滋病病毒如此难以消灭? "),a])}const u=o(s,[["render",d],["__file","21-HIV-Kill.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
